Located on the Paul Bunyan Scenic Byway, Crosslake is home to 14 island studded lakes known as the Whitefish Chain, not to mention a rich history of Indian lore and logging. Explore unique shops, great golfing and delicious food.  A 25-minute drive northeast of nearby Brainerd Minnesota, Crosslake is a year round vacation destination.
Rent a surrey bike for the ultimate way to get around town.  Bike and walking paths are found throughout the city.

Stop by the Crosslake Historic Log Village to learn more about the area history.  The Chamber of Commerce office is staffed during the summer months with retired volunteers that know the area inside and out.

Stop in at Crosslake Town Square all summer long on Saturdays 6PM to 8PM for free entertainment.  Bring your lawn chair and enjoy!  Great for adults and kids (and grandkids).  Raffertys Pizza and Chocolate Ox Icecream available.  Lots of other distinctive shops in the Town Square.

Visit Lakes Area Gallery in Crosslake Town Square.  They offer a diverse selection of originals, limited edition prints and canvases and poster prints.  They are professional picture framers using conservation materials and techniques.  An eclectic line of home decor is also offered.
